<br>
Please remove the restrictions on our charming.  We should be the enchanters of animal charming.  Our pets should be buffable and healable by other classes.  Anything an enchanter has in the way of charm, we should have for animals.  It seems to me to be more than appropriate that a druid would have MORE charm abilities for animals than an enchanter has for normal mobs.  Level 53 seems like an absolute cap that's too low.  Level 46 for dire charm is laughable.<br>
<br>
While you're at it, how about actually putting all animals in the animal class.  Raptors are animals.  Cockatrices look like animals to me too.  And all walking ape types, named or not.  Please make them all druid charmable.  And if you're going to make our only plant charm spell horribly low level, please make all plants count as animals too.  Fungi are also part of nature -- you know, mushrooms that walk and hit you.<br>
<br>
Also, aren't we supposed to be masters of nature?  I really don't think wolf and tree form are all the forms of nature.  L*O*T*S MORE FORM OF ((( X ))) SPELLS PLEASE!<br>
<br>
