60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New Spells for druids: A suggestion</span><hr size=1> Since i find myself most often used as a backup healer, and taking care of light tanks i would love to see something like this.<br>
<br>
Natures Recovery, single target 240 mana, heal over time(4ticks) 1200hps - no penalties. - its basicly a copy of topor, with a little higher mana cost due to the no penalty, considering shamans actually converts topor to extra mana, its in no way overpowering.<br>
<br>
Natures rejuvination(i suck at titles, sue me), Group version, 800mana, for 1200hps healed to each member of your group over 4 ticks.<br>
<br>
Natures touch to be a copy of the cleric Divine light in mana cost. screw the small penalty, they can keep that edge.<br>
<br>
Clerics whining because they arent needed in a group and that they are only a raid class if we gets improvements on the healing area - can shut it, shamans already got it. and it didnt affect them, simply because nothing replaces that rez stick, or complete heal for that matter.<br>
<br>
It would simply enable us to effectively keep a group alive.<br>
<br>
Another idea (that i shamelessly ripped off from some post on this board)<br>
<br>
Healing shield.(aka reversed damage shield, and no its not a copy of mark of karn)<br>
<br>
Casted on a player, and each time he gets hit, he gets a fixed amount of hps back, the highest version could be 100+hps, <br>
Duration 20 seconds, recast time 60 seconds. mana cost 250.<br>
<br>
point with the last spell is, If we wanna have some improvements on our raid area,<br>
We need something unique and needed, bit like shamans have slow,  clerics got CH, and enchanter got clarity and haste, and we need to be the best at it, im sure someone could come up with something better but here it is.<br>
<br>
And no, i dont want to see more ideas for ressist buffs :P<br>
<br>
play around with it for a bit.<br>
